http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 1 Jul 2021
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2021 [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=35380


Classical swine fever virus (inf. with), Bhutan
--------------------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 23 Jun 2021
Confirmed: 23 Jun 2021
Reported: 30 Jun 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 29 Jun 2018
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: classical swine fever virus [CSFV]
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Samtenling, Chang, Thimphu
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 Jun 2021
Epidemiological unit: forest
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Wild boar (_Sus scrofa_): Suidae-Artiodactyla / - / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: Affected population were the wild boars reported to have died in the forest surrounding Samtenling area, located in the periphery of the Thimphu city, Bhutan.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Wild boar die-offs were reported from the forests around Samtenling area in the periphery of Thimphu City, Bhutan. No morbidity or mortality were observed during the outbreak investigation in the area; however, the surveillance team could pick 2 wild boar carcasses which have started putrefying. Bone marrow samples were extracted and subjected to RT-PCR test for classical swine fever and resulted positive.

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone; traceability; zoning; ante- and post-mortem inspections

Wild control measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone; traceability; zoning; ante- and post-mortem inspections; disinfection; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Centre for Animal Health (NCAH) (national laboratory) / wild boar / real-time multiplex polymerase chain reaction (real-time multiplex PCR) / 23 Jun 2021 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

